column1: # Title: Coefficients of freight inputs to energy and ag commodities
# Units: million tkm per EJ = ton-meters per GJ
# Comments: price-unit-conversion takes into account the following:
#  (1) transportation output unit is 1e6 times the price unit denominator whereas all other sectors are 1e9.
#  (2) transportation price unit is 1990$ whereas others are 1975$.
#  (3) trn_freight costs are 17x higher than rail mode (the dominant mode for some of these fuels). Some de-rating is appropriate.
# Note: the methods are not set up to handle different tkm inputs for different refined liquid fuel commodities (e.g.
